Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Mince @cilantro{¼%ounce}(minced). Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced or grated). Zest and halve @lemon{1}(zested and halved). Mince @jalapeño{1}(minced and seeded for less heat). Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%can}(drained and rinsed).

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water. Pat shrimp dry with #paper towels{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add ¼ of the onion; cook, stirring, until just softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in 1 cup water (2 cups for 4 servings), half the @veggie stock concentrate{2}, and a pinch of salt; bring to a boil. Add @quinoa{½%cup}; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until quinoa is tender and water has absorbed, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While quinoa cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine cilantro, @olive oil{2%tbsp} (3 TBSP for 4 servings), a pinch of garlic, salt, and pepper. Add lemon juice to taste and as much jalapeño as you like. Taste and add more garlic if desired.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp}, a pinch of salt, and as much lemon zest as you like. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add shrimp; cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in the large pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and remaining onion. Cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes} (7-10 minutes for 4 servings).

Add @Tunisian spice blend{1%tbsp}, remaining garlic, and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Use pan used for shrimp here.

Add ⅓ cup water (⅔ cup for 4 servings) and remaining stock concentrates to pan with veggies.

Stir in chickpeas and bring tagine to a low simmer. Cook until liquid has slightly reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir in shrimp along with chickpeas.

Fluff quinoa with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide quinoa between plates and top with tagine, @sliced almonds{½%ounce}, and @dried apricots{1%ounce}.

> TIP: Toast almonds before adding if you like.

Drizzle with lemon crema and chermoula. Drizzle with @?hot sauce{1%tsp} if desired. Cut any remaining lemon into wedges and serve on the side.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.